{"award_age":54.0,"bio_image":"full\/740983533439eafd4c3807af19e0cd14f38e590f.jpg","category":"Chemistry","country":"United States","date_of_birth":"1926-06-30T00:00:00.000Z","date_of_death":null,"gender":"male","image_urls":["http:\/\/upload.wikimedia.org\/wikipedia\/commons\/thumb\/8\/88\/Paul_Berg_in_1980.jpg\/250px-Paul_Berg_in_1980.jpg"],"link":"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Paul_Berg","mini_bio":"<p><b>Paul Berg<\/b> (born June 30, 1926) is an <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/United_States\" title=\"United States\">American<\/a> <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemist\" title=\"Biochemist\">biochemist<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Professor_emeritus\" title=\"Professor emeritus\" class=\"mw-redirect\">professor emeritus<\/a> at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stanford_University\" title=\"Stanford University\">Stanford University<\/a>. He was the recipient of the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry\" title=\"Nobel Prize in Chemistry\">Nobel Prize in Chemistry<\/a> in 1980, along with <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Walter_Gilbert\" title=\"Walter Gilbert\">Walter Gilbert<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Frederick_Sanger\" title=\"Frederick Sanger\">Frederick Sanger<\/a>. The award recognized their contributions to basic research involving <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Nucleic_acid\" title=\"Nucleic acid\">nucleic acids<\/a>. Berg received his undergraduate education at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Pennsylvania_State_University\" title=\"Pennsylvania State University\">Penn State University<\/a>, where he majored in <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Biochemistry\" title=\"Biochemistry\">biochemistry<\/a>. He received his <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Doctor_of_Philosophy\" title=\"Doctor of Philosophy\">Ph.D.<\/a> in biochemistry from <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Case_Western_Reserve_University\" title=\"Case Western Reserve University\">Case Western Reserve University<\/a> in 1952. Berg worked as a professor at <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Washington_University_School_of_Medicine\" title=\"Washington University School of Medicine\">Washington University School of Medicine<\/a> and <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Stanford_University_School_of_Medicine\" title=\"Stanford University School of Medicine\">Stanford University School of Medicine<\/a>, in addition to serving as the director of the Beckman Center for Molecular and Genetic Medicine. In addition to the Nobel Prize, Berg was presented with the <a href=\"http:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/National_Medal_of_Science\" title=\"National Medal of Science\">National Medal of Science<\/a> in 1983 and the National Library of Medicine Medal in 1986.<\/p>","name":"Paul Berg","place_of_birth":"Brooklyn ,  New York","place_of_death":null,"text":"Paul Berg , Chemistry, 1980","year":1980.0}